---
import DocsLayout from '../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro'
const brewInstall = 'brew install santi020k/tap/santi020k-terminal && santi020k-terminal install'
const scriptInstall = 'curl --proto \'=https\' --tlsv1.2 -fsSL https://terminal.santi020k.com/zsh/install.zsh | zsh'
const headings = [{ id: 'requirements', label: 'Requirements' }, { id: 'homebrew', label: 'Install with Homebrew' }, { id: 'script', label: 'Install script' }, { id: 'next-steps', label: 'Next steps' }]
---
<DocsLayout title="Installation" description="Install the complete Santi020k terminal setup on macOS with Homebrew or the hosted setup script." path="/docs/installation/" {headings}>
  <aside class="docs-callout"><b>Homebrew is recommended</b><p>It owns the CLI, theme assets, shell completions, and dependencies, making updates and removal predictable.</p></aside>
  <section id="requirements"><h2>Requirements</h2><ul><li>macOS with Zsh as the interactive shell.</li><li>Homebrew installed and available in your shell.</li><li>A Nerd Font if you use the Powerline prompt symbols.</li></ul></section>
  <section id="homebrew"><h2>Install with Homebrew</h2><p>Install the formula, then explicitly apply the managed configuration:</p><div class="command"><code>{brewInstall}</code><button data-copy={brewInstall} aria-label="Copy Homebrew installation command">Copy</button></div><p>The installer backs up files it manages, writes configuration to <code>~/.config/santi020k-terminal</code>, and adds one source line to <code>~/.zshrc</code>. Start a new session with <code>exec zsh</code>.</p></section>
  <section id="script"><h2>Install with the hosted script</h2><p>This path installs the same Homebrew dependencies and downloads the current configuration directly:</p><div class="command"><code>{scriptInstall}</code><button data-copy={scriptInstall} aria-label="Copy hosted installation command">Copy</button></div><p><a href="/zsh/install.zsh">Read the installer source</a> before running it if you want to inspect every operation.</p></section>
  <section id="next-steps"><h2>Next steps</h2><div class="docs-link-list"><a href="/docs/zsh/"><b>Understand the Zsh setup</b><span>Plugins, tools, history, and managed configuration.</span></a><a href="/docs/cli/"><b>Learn the CLI</b><span>Switch presets, install colors, check status, or repair the setup.</span></a></div></section>
</DocsLayout>
